<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Friday morning news posts from Gordon</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=210958" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/006971.html">Hello Gordon, remember this? (Iksar armor)</a></B><P>

Gordon, I must admit that I have faith that Verant will (eventually) address this issue. <P>

<B>Thanks for bringing the issue back up, and I can let you know that there is forward progress being made on this issue. The biggest problem that we've identified and taken steps to correct is a gap between smithed armor, and Jarsath, that is at around 20 levels wide. <P>

I reviewed the item list for 3 sets of class-specific armor three days ago, and the quests are now being written.<P>

As for planar type equivalents, evalutation of that end of item availability is behind the mid-level stuff in priority. One we get these quests in we'll start looking at the other end of the spectrum.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009976.html">How to get a ressurection</a></B><P>

I am Aenae Webspinner, a 50th level Priestess of Innoruuk on the Luclin server, and I want to share a little information with you about experience ressurections.<P>

1. The key to getting my attention is politeness. Be polite, ask nicely, and if I have time I'll help you out.<P>

<B>Aenae_Luclin,<P>

As someone who's seen /petitions that read, "Soandso won't give me a rez", I thank you for helping the community out.<P>

Please allow me to add my own tip:<P>

9. Forcing the cleric in your group to /random for cleric spells or cleric loot that is dropped could hurt your chances of getting a rez in the future.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010023.html">Rogue Rocks !!... rock what?</a></B><P>

What! Rogues don't suck. Rogues do rock! Great damage output, hide/sneak, evade is very cool, our class armor is dropped ~ not quested, our quest weapon is decent ~ not sucky... it's posts like this that keep slamming rogues back down. If you keep saying we suck, people will keep believing it. The rogue class has had many upgrades, all positive, and we are now a very effective fighting machine. This rogue has no complaints!<P>

<B>My feelings exactly (though I do know that some consider it a disadvantage to have dropped armor rather than quested). And don't forget poison :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010025.html">Gordon is mis-informed.</a></B><P>

Not true, my most recently ignored post was on how a players pet had been hanging around in Najena for hours after the player had went LD and the pet attacked and killed me. So pets CAN and DO stay in the world after the player leaves. The GM said that this was a "game feature" and i could not receive a res..although the GM killed the "rogue" pet because he said it didn't belong there.<P>

<B>Rogue pets aren't "pets" from a game mechanics perspective. A pet is an NPC that is owned by another entity. Rogue pets aren't owned as such, and ownership can't be reapplied once it is lost.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010113.html">What does it take to get a reply from Gordon??</a></B><P>

I feel as if I've had several relevant questions about EQ that were ignored... never gotten a reply no matter how polite i've been...<P>

<B>Gossamer, I just looked for some of the posts you've made but only find this one since the boards were pruned. If it's any solace, I don't remember purposely ignoring any of your posts :)</B><P>

What does it take to get a reply from Gordon??<P>

<B>Well first I have to see it. I can't really give you any pointers on getting that done. Most days I pick a page between 1 and 10, answer a bunch of posts, then just refresh the thread index on that page. I usually come to the front two pages to check and see if anything new and interesting has popped up.<P>

Lately, I've been spending more time addressing posts that end up down on page 10 without anyone noticing them.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010130.html">possible way to get gloves to proc ABASHI i qoute you in here</a></B><P>

If the combat system does indeed go to an equipment slot to see if your gloves are magical whenever you punch could the programmers add a few lines of code there so that whenever the combat system checks for magic status it could also do a test to see if the gloves proc an effect?<P>

<B>These are very different situations, and I'm sorry but I can't explain it much more detail. In the case you mentioned, the hand, foot, shoulder slots are not accessed upon each hit. The ability of a character to hit, kick, slam magic creatures is set for the character upon equipping or removing the item, rather than by accessing the item upon each combat round. Sometimes the way something appears to work isn't the way it works from a mechanics standpoint. It's sort of like us being unable to make potions stackable. The fact that alcohol is stackable and activatable is completely separate from the idea of making potions that are stackable and activatable. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010131.html">Two little questions</a></B><P>

1) Did you say that the pop up adds were going to be removed from the page? I hope so, you are going to get me in trouble at work.<P>

<B>Yes, our ad people are all over it. No popup ads are supposed to be displayed in any game forum. They're the quickest way to chase away visitors, which we certainly don't want to do.</B><P>

2) This is probaby considered a closed issue, but what are the chances of getting Roror super buffed and put back on Beta Neutral. I am soon going to give up on cazic all together. I love that zone, but of course have to leave every now and then to sell, bank, quest, fight with guild mates, etc...<P>

<B>Actually something along these lines occurred about 2 or 3 patches ago.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010135.html">A request for Patch Announcement and a comment on GODS !!! all you now mid 40's read</a></B><P>

I find the constant posting of patches in either PDT, EST, PST ? its all lost on me. I’m sure a lot of us out there would appreciate this.<P>

<B>We're GMT-8, meaning that it's 8 hours later in Greenwich. As far as posting it, we want to try and confuse the smallest number of people possible. For part of the world, we don't even get the date right as it is :)</B><P>

its unfair to a HUGE amount of players who potentially after upwards of a years play will just be approaching the level required to encounter Gods<P>

<B>I understand your feelings on this. Frankly, could it be avoided we would. From an RP perspective, across many fantasy worlds created in novels and such, the power of a deity is based upon the number or strength of their followers. That's basically what's happening in Norrath, a combination of both.<P>

From a loot perspective, we will indeed be moving thier current loot down to creatures powered similarly to what the deities are now. The deities will be populated with level 60 loot and become an appropriate encounter for a large group in that level range. Indeed, this will raise the bar for encountering a deity, however killing deities is supposed to be the pinnacle of success in EverQuest. So is encountering dragons, however in that case we decided to place the level cap on the old dragons to keep them within reach.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010136.html">Some good thoughts here what do you think Absahi?</a></B><P>

Most of the people in the following thread encouragingly enough support an AC upgrade for us.<P>

<B>The issue is that monks stack up in AC versus the other classes right where they should right now, equipped in full shiverback. Going to some of the more mundane items that have been suggested actually gives them more ac than they should have. As I mentioned before, the problem is not that shiverback's ac is too low, but the other stuff mentioned has ac that is too high, from the monk's perspective due to their innate AC bonus. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010141.html">Dont ban dupers, this is even worse</a></B><P>

Try this instead, when a player is caught duping, you tell him that he has been caught, on from now on you are gonna log EVERYTHING he is gonna do ingame(that character only). Plus he is not allowed to do ANYTHING with the duped items. This includes not being allowed to delete them, move them around in his inventory, or drop them. if he does any of this it will be a banning offence. In many cases they will just delete the caracter, but that function should be disabled. if you do this, then the Dupers would be given a chance to better themselves, but will forever have to live with their mistake, in that the character will be there every time they log in.<P>

<B>I think that it would take considerably less effort on our part and be considerably better for the game just to release someone like that rather than toying with them like a cat with a mouse. We'd rather the GMs spend time helping out customers we want to keep.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
